If the drawings and specifications are signed by the author thereof with the true titles of their occupations as may be required by law, this chapter does not apply to:
Any building which is to be used for farm purposes only;
Any residential structure that does not require the services or seal of an architect or engineer either under the Uniform State Building Code pursuant to KRS 198B.050 or under KRS 323.033;
Any building classified by use group other than those listed under KRS 323.033 so long as the services or seal of an architect or engineer as applicable is not required for such other use group under the Uniform State Building Code pursuant to KRS 198B.050 or;
Any structure not classified as a building by KRS 323.010(4).

Provisions of this chapter shall not apply to:
Any individual, partnership, or firm acting solely as a consultant to an architect licensed in the Commonwealth;
An architect or other person acting solely as an officer or employee of the United States government.
